qas.question: Who was with Nasser when he died?

answers.text: Heikal, Sadat, and Nasser's wife Tahia

qas.question: What health events had Nasser suffered in 1966 and 1969?
How old were Nasser's brothers when they died?

context: As the summit closed on <a0_0>28 September 1970<a0_0/>, hours after escorting the last Arab leader to leave, Nasser suffered a <a1_0>heart attack<a1_0/>. He was immediately transported to his house, where his physicians tended to him. Nasser died several hours later, around 6:00 p.m. <a2_0>Heikal, Sadat, and Nasser's wife Tahia<a2_0/> were at his deathbed. According to his doctor, al-Sawi Habibi, Nasser's likely cause of death was arteriosclerosis, varicose veins, and complications from long-standing diabetes. Nasser was a heavy smoker with a family history of heart disease—two of his brothers died <a4_0>in their fifties<a4_0/> from the same condition. The state of Nasser's health was not known to the public prior to his death. He had previously suffered <a3_0>heart attacks<a3_0/> in 1966 and September 1969.
